register

public boolean register()
Description copied from interface: InterfaceController
Register the controller with its targets.

All controllers must register with their targets in order to be allowed to manipulate them. This is to prevent clashes, in which two or more controllers access the same variable. Use Controller.registerFlowController(edu.berkeley.path.beats.simulator.Link, int) Controller.registerSpeedController(edu.berkeley.path.beats.simulator.Link, int) to register. The return value of these methods indicates whether the registration was successful.

Returns:
true if the controller successfully registered with all of its targets; false otherwise.

update

public void update()
Description copied from interface: InterfaceComponent
Update the state of the component.

Called by Scenario.run(edu.berkeley.path.beats.simulator.SimulationSettings, java.util.Properties) at each simulation time step. This function updates the internal state of the component.

Because events are state-less, the Event class provides a default implementation of this method, so it need not be implemented by other event classes.

deregister

public boolean deregister()
Description copied from interface: InterfaceController
deRegister the controller with its targets.

All controllers must deregister with their targets when they are no longer active This is to prevent clashes, in which two or more controllers access the same variable at different simulation periods . Use Controller.deregisterFlowController(edu.berkeley.path.beats.simulator.Link) Controller.deregisterSpeedController(edu.berkeley.path.beats.simulator.Link) to register. The return value of these methods indicates whether the deregistration was successful.

Returns:
true if the controller successfully registered with all of its targets; false otherwise.
